Edition:
Quote: To refer to a person, to his disadvantage, with the third person. .in 4;`You'd made it look as if I'd been having a good time with Val while she was away. You silly bastard, now you've put me in crook with her.'
Notes: (1962-63)1974 Syder and Hodgetts Aust and NZ English [TS] 895

